PKS (Pivotal Container Service) is used to create and manage on-demand Kubernetes clusters via the PKS CLI.

## <a id="v1.1.0"></a>v1.1.0

**Release Date**: TBD, 2018

<p class="note breaking"><strong>Breaking Change</strong>: PKS CLI prompts for confirmation before resizing clusters, since this is a non-reversable action. The CLI supports a `--non-interactive` flag to skip this interactive confirmation. </p>

